verses.roman:
āge śuna jagannāthera guṇḍicā-gamana
tāra āge prabhu yaiche karilā nartana

synonyms: āge—ahead; śuna—hear; jagannāthera—of Lord Jagannātha; guṇḍicā-gamana—going to the Guṇḍicā temple; tāra āge—before that; prabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; yaiche—as; karilā—did; nartana—dancing.
translation: Now please hear about Lord Jagannātha's going to the Guṇḍicā temple while Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu danced before the Ratha car.
